<br>
This is not a rant, but an observation:<br>
<br>
Expanding the level range opens up places like Seb and Velks to the 65's again. The biggest benefit is more for the 62's in these zones I would assume. <br>
<br>
When Sony did this, they forgot that there was an influx of people who are tired of LFG and those people would now have the option at least to go back to some of their old haunts. <br>
<br>
The forgotten part was that most of those zones were already being utilized by the level 50-60 groups and now those people can't compete for the spawns.<br>
<br>
Add to that the fact that the (some) flags are gone and you have a lot of low players fighting in zones that should have been left to the higher players and it becomes a nightmare. <br>
<br>
A level 62 cleric can't get a PoS group as her spot is held by a twinked 54 cleric bot. So she decides to go to a lower zone to get some exp rather than have the night be a write-off. <br>
<br>
That now pushes the next lowest cleric or group down the food chain due to the spawn rates being too low to support such an influx. <br>
<br>
I am 4 blues from 60 and this isn't a big deal for me personally because in 2 days I will be one of those people pulling spawns away from those lower players.<br>
<br>
Now if Sony had thought to open up the entire range of experience gained, areas like Lguk, DL and other popular areas would again become viable for those under 60 in level.<br>
<br>
Sony would have found alot of old underutilized zones coming back to life. I realize about the changes to nurga etc, but I am referring to ALL zones.<br>
<br>
It wouldn't be that hard to make the change viable for all to enjoy and I would bet 99% of the EQ population would agree with it. <br>
<br>
The only flaw to such a move would be high ZEM zones like paludal Caverns filling with noobs and not having them leave until 35 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rotfl --><img src=http://smilies.crowd9.com/contrib/geno/rofl.gif ALT=":rotfl"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
An across the board change in experience would have been the best thing they could have done.<br>
<br>
I really do feel bad for those trying to eek out experience with 15 level 63's in an old world zone or for those that have 64's pulling rats and flies like they are killing orcs in EC.<br>
<br>
How would you guys have handled the change?<br>
<br>
