<br>
As a reasonably geared 59 cleric with 17AA I have the option of around 12 decent XP zones for grouping, and about half a dozen I can solo in.  When the rush dies down in the new zone under LOIO i'll be trying that too, it looks like a good spot for a 59 cleric to solo, light blue to 65th so low blue to me - and groups of undead mobs.<br>
<br>
My 55th Enchanter could do the lower tiers (if I bothered to buy pop on her account) but instead I preffer the old world dungeons because there's more for a chanter to do - I like to be challenged (or I enjoy CR's one of the two!) and I have the choice of Chardok, Sebelis, Velks, and Karnors Castle.  None are particularly good XP - but they are fun to play and I enjoy them because of all the adds.<br>
<br>
However my 51st Shadow Knight is a bit stumped.  If a group would take me I can get excellent XP in Dreadlands by fighting trains.  Those who have grouped with me there sing in joy as to the XP they get from a 6 mob fight.  I'll pull more if there's a chanter.  However few people think they will get good XP with a 51 SK so it's hard to convince people i'll get a group.  If I goto Velks, Sebelis or Chardok I get sidelined as an also-ran melee, and Karnors is proving to be very similar.  I've tried LFG in PoP to much the same result.  There isn't anywhere I can go that gives more than a 10% chance of a group.<br>
<br>
It's my opinion that the low 50's are very much shafted at the moment.  I remember when AA was introduced and my cleric was low 50 at the time - I went two months with barely a group so that's when I started learning to solo.  Sebelis and Chardok where the LFG zones of the day, and I couldn't get a group in either for all the 60 clerics getting their AA.  Much the same is still true for the low 50's even before this recent change.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I think expanding the range of experience gain will be a good thing for this reason.  I also think the range should be expanded for another reason though, and one that is far more important.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Many of my RL friends play EQ, and i've many friends from ingame that I like to play with.  Since PoP came along i've not grouped with an old warrior friend at all because he is much further into his PoP progression than I am.  I have a couple of friends who are a little lower, and grouping with them is difficult because our level range is so stretched out that none of us really get decent XP together.<br>
<br>
