<br>
yah, i agree verant fubar'ed this expansion...  originally it was hyped as &quot;the solution to raid-only high end content&quot;, where high lvls could hunt properly lvl mobs without requiring 12-30 peeps to do it.  problem was, you still needed at least that many to secure key/flags to 80% of the content.  great solution. NOT.  then they remove keys from about 40% of the content and its going to screw things up until the dust settles.  eventually those &quot;first timers&quot; in the &quot;new&quot; pop zones will die a few times and understand &quot;maybe they should wait a couple lvls&quot;.<br>
<br>
my guild did an exploratory run into CoD other day [before they lifted the flag, we were keyed via the quest].  avg lvl of group was about 58, and we killed a couple of mobs, but wiped on a 2 pull, since the enchanter couldnt mezz them (lvl restriciton on his mezz i guess).  so we decided we'd try again in a couple lvls and accepted the position of hanging in Tier 1 until more of us were 60+.  others will learn this lesson and after a few weeks it will go back to business as usual.  in the mean time, take a tour of history during those long LFG bouts and grab a friend and go harass ME, DN, Kael, Icewell Keep, AC, etc.  because i'm sure you'll find you have little competition for spawns and camps.<br>
<br>
